+    G_tmpl(F_SL(1/16); I) = (1/4, 49/256)
+
+  on I = [0,1],
+
+  so the repaired template-defect sheet is attained sharply by the carried
+  friendly witness?
+  ```
+
+- `[INFERRED]` Smallest meaningful carried-forward test object:
+  the single exact witness
+  `F_SL(1/16)`.
+  Carrying the whole `F_SL(rho)` interval forward would already overclaim past
+  the explicit Step-4 / Step-5 witness record.
+- `[VERIFIED]` Invariant observable the next phase must use:
+  the same repaired defect observable
+  `G_tmpl(P_n; I) = (Delta_tmpl, Delta_spec)`
+  on the frozen role hierarchy sheet
+  `(h_seed, h_clk, h_amp, h_rot, h_next) = (1/16, 1/4, 1, 2, 2)`
+  with `eps_ref = 1/64`.
+- `[INFERRED]` Exact missing data before that theorem claim would be honest:
+  1. one explicit `sigma_SL` / `phi_SL` coefficient-sign ledger for the carried
+     witness on the frozen role order;
+  2. one exact role-projected forcing table
+     `(Q_clk, Q_seed, Q_amp, Q_rot^D, Q_rot^A, Q_next)` for that witness on
+     `I = [0,1]`;
+  3. one exact derivation of where the suprema in `Delta_tmpl` and
+     `Delta_spec` are achieved, rather than only a dossier-level diagnostic
+     vector; and
+  4. one exact confirmation that the forced spectator channels contributing to
+     `Delta_spec` are exactly the frozen completion classes and no larger
+     packet rewrite is being used.
+- `[INFERRED]` Strongest claim this object is allowed to support now:
+  the repaired template-defect sheet has one carried exact friendly boundary
+  witness on the audited ledger, namely `F_SL(1/16)`.
+- `[VERIFIED]` What the local record still does **not** justify:
+  a theorem for all `F_SL(rho)`,
+  an explicit hostile template-defect counterexample on a concrete `F_DT`
+  packet,
+  or any theorem statement outside the frozen packet class, fixed window, and
+  repaired defect sheet.
