+# Exploration 002 Summary
+
+## Goal
+
+Attach one first exact theorem question or one first exact counterexample-search
+question to each promoted Step-6 survivor on the repaired frozen packet ledger.
+
+## What I Tried
+
+- Read the controlling Step-6 goal together with the Step-5 repaired shortlist,
+  the Step-4 packet dossier, the Step-2 gate definitions, and the cited
+  factual/meta guardrails.
+- Checked which carried-forward witness or hostile slice is smallest enough for
+  an honest next test without reopening packet search or widening the audited
+  family.
+- Separated what each survivor can support now from what would still be only a
+  dossier-level insertion line.
+
+## Outcome
+
+- Status: `succeeded`.
+- Repaired `Template-Defect Near-Closure` gets a first exact **theorem
+  question** on the single carried witness `F_SL(1/16)`:
+  prove exact boundary saturation
+  `G_tmpl(F_SL(1/16); I) = (1/4, 49/256)`.
+- Repaired `Windowed Spectator-Leakage Budget` gets a first exact
+  **counterexample-search question** on the single audited hostile packet
+  `F_DT(1/16, 1/256)`:
+  compute `G_leak` exactly and exhibit one repaired-budget violation.
+
+## Key Takeaway
+
+The honest Step-6 handoff is asymmetric:
+the template object is ready only for a smallest friendly boundary theorem
+test, while the leakage object is ready for a smallest explicit hostile
+counterexample search.
+
+## Leads Worth Pursuing
+
+- For `Template-Defect Near-Closure`, write the exact `sigma_SL` / `phi_SL`
+  coefficient ledger and derive the role-projected forcing table needed to
+  prove the boundary value `(1/4, 49/256)` on `F_SL(1/16)`.
+- For `Windowed Spectator-Leakage Budget`, write one explicit
+  `sigma_DT` wavevector / helicity ledger for `F_DT(1/16, 1/256)` and derive
+  the exact classwise integrals in the frozen
+  `mirror` / `companion` / `feedback` / `cross` partition.
+
+## Unexpected Findings
+
+- The two survivors should remain distinct at Step 6 because their first honest
+  next tests point in opposite directions:
+  friendly boundary sharpness versus hostile explicit overload.
+- Family-wide questions would already overclaim for both objects on the present
+  record, even though both survivors remain live.
+
+## Computations Worth Doing Later
+
+- For the template object:
+  exact supremum-time evaluation for `Delta_tmpl` and `Delta_spec` on the
+  carried witness `F_SL(1/16)`.
+- For the leakage object:
+  exact classwise integrated ledger and `int_I D_on = 1` normalization check
+  on `F_DT(1/16, 1/256)`.
