+# Exploration 002 Report
+
+## Goal
+
+Attach one first exact next-test assignment to each promoted Step-6 object on the frozen packet ledger:
+
+- repaired `Template-Defect Near-Closure`
+- repaired `Windowed Spectator-Leakage Budget`
+
+For each object, identify the smallest carried-forward test object or family, the exact invariant/admissibility sheet for the next phase, the exact missing data still needed before any honest theorem or counterexample claim, and the strongest claim currently supported.
+
+## Sources Used
+
+- `steps/step-006/GOAL.md`
+- `steps/step-005/RESULTS.md`
+- `steps/step-005/explorations/exploration-003/REPORT.md`
+- `steps/step-004/RESULTS.md`
+- `steps/step-003/RESULTS.md`
+- `steps/step-002/RESULTS.md`
+- required library inbox and factual/meta notes listed in the task prompt
+
+## Working Notes
+
+### Initial setup
+
+- Created report skeleton before substantive analysis.
+- Read the controlling Step-6 goal, the Step-5 repaired shortlist, the Step-4
+  dossier, the Step-2 gate definitions, and the cited factual/meta notes
+  before assigning any next test.
+
+## Findings
+
+### 1. Controlling frozen ledger for this exploration
+
+- `[VERIFIED]` Both promoted objects remain on the same audited packet class:
+  the canonical one-bridge role-labeled helical packet family with mandatory
+  conjugate completion.
+- `[VERIFIED]` Both objects inherit the same fixed Tao-like interaction core:
+  `A -> B`,
+  `A -> C`,
+  `B,C -> C`,
+  `C,A <-> D`,
+  `D,D -> E`.
+- `[VERIFIED]` Both objects inherit the same forced spectator classes:
+  `mirror`,
+  `companion`,
+  `feedback`,
+  `cross`.
+- `[VERIFIED]` Both objects stay on the same fixed window, canonical gauge,
+  role order, sign sheet policy, and phase anchor policy. No Step-6 next test
+  may widen the packet family or soften the repaired thresholds.
+
+### 2. Repaired `Template-Defect Near-Closure` gets a first exact theorem question
+
+- `[VERIFIED]` The repaired admissibility sheet is
+
+  ```text
+  G_tmpl(P_n; I) = (Delta_tmpl, Delta_spec),
+  Delta_tmpl <= 1/4,
+  Delta_spec <= 49/256.
+  ```
+
+- `[VERIFIED]` Step 5 already identifies
+  `F_SL(1/16)`
+  as the smallest carried-forward friendly witness:
+  it is the worst recorded friendly packet on both repaired defect
+  coordinates.
+- `[INFERRED]` The first honest next test is therefore a **theorem question on
+  one explicit boundary witness**, not a family-wide theorem and not a hostile
+  package claim:
+
+  ```text
+  On the frozen packet ledger, can one prove exactly that
+
+    G_tmpl(F_SL(1/16); I) = (1/4, 49/256)
+
+  on I = [0,1],
+
+  so the repaired template-defect sheet is attained sharply by the carried
+  friendly witness?
+  ```
+
+- `[INFERRED]` Smallest meaningful carried-forward test object:
+  the single exact witness
+  `F_SL(1/16)`.
+  Carrying the whole `F_SL(rho)` interval forward would already overclaim past
+  the explicit Step-4 / Step-5 witness record.
+- `[VERIFIED]` Invariant observable the next phase must use:
+  the same repaired defect observable
+  `G_tmpl(P_n; I) = (Delta_tmpl, Delta_spec)`
+  on the frozen role hierarchy sheet
+  `(h_seed, h_clk, h_amp, h_rot, h_next) = (1/16, 1/4, 1, 2, 2)`
+  with `eps_ref = 1/64`.
+- `[INFERRED]` Exact missing data before that theorem claim would be honest:
+  1. one explicit `sigma_SL` / `phi_SL` coefficient-sign ledger for the carried
+     witness on the frozen role order;
+  2. one exact role-projected forcing table
+     `(Q_clk, Q_seed, Q_amp, Q_rot^D, Q_rot^A, Q_next)` for that witness on
+     `I = [0,1]`;
+  3. one exact derivation of where the suprema in `Delta_tmpl` and
+     `Delta_spec` are achieved, rather than only a dossier-level diagnostic
+     vector; and
+  4. one exact confirmation that the forced spectator channels contributing to
+     `Delta_spec` are exactly the frozen completion classes and no larger
+     packet rewrite is being used.
+- `[INFERRED]` Strongest claim this object is allowed to support now:
+  the repaired template-defect sheet has one carried exact friendly boundary
+  witness on the audited ledger, namely `F_SL(1/16)`.
+- `[VERIFIED]` What the local record still does **not** justify:
+  a theorem for all `F_SL(rho)`,
+  an explicit hostile template-defect counterexample on a concrete `F_DT`
+  packet,
+  or any theorem statement outside the frozen packet class, fixed window, and
+  repaired defect sheet.
+
+### 3. Repaired `Windowed Spectator-Leakage Budget` gets a first exact counterexample-search question
+
+- `[VERIFIED]` The repaired admissibility sheet is
+
+  ```text
+  G_leak(P_n; I) = (L_tot, L_mirror, L_companion, L_feedback, L_cross)
+
+  with budgets
+
+    (1/4, 1/12, 1/12, 1/16, 1/24).
+  ```
+
+- `[VERIFIED]` This remains the sharpest same-currency obstruction-facing gate
+  on the frozen ledger.
+- `[VERIFIED]` The Step-4 family ledger already freezes the smallest audited
+  hostile grid for the comparator family:
+  `delta in {1/16, 1/8}`,
+  `eta in {1/256, 1/128}`.
+- `[INFERRED]` The first honest next test is therefore a **counterexample
+  search on one explicit hostile grid point**, not a family-wide hostile
+  theorem:
+
+  ```text
+  At the smallest audited hostile packet F_DT(1/16, 1/256),
+  can one compute G_leak exactly on the frozen ledger and exhibit at least one
+  repaired-budget violation, preferably a companion or feedback overload, so
+  that the branch lands its first explicit hostile counterexample packet?
+  ```
+
+- `[INFERRED]` Smallest meaningful carried-forward test object:
+  the single audited hostile packet
+  `F_DT(1/16, 1/256)`.
+  One explicit hostile packet is enough for the first honest counterexample
+  search; there is no need to reopen the whole two-parameter family first.
+- `[VERIFIED]` Admissibility sheet the next phase must use:
+  the same repaired classwise leakage ledger
+  `G_leak(P_n; I)`
+  with the frozen spectator partition and the same fixed window `I = [0,1]`.
+- `[INFERRED]` Exact missing data before that counterexample claim would be
+  honest:
+  1. one concrete `sigma_DT` wavevector / helicity / sign ledger for the chosen
+     grid point, since the repo still records the hostile packet mostly at the
+     dossier level;
+  2. one exact integrated class ledger
+     `(int_I D_mirror, int_I D_companion, int_I D_feedback, int_I D_cross)`
+     derived from that packet rather than cited abstractly;
+  3. one exact normalization check that the same packet satisfies
+     `int_I D_on = 1` on the frozen window; and
+  4. one exact routing table from raw forced channels into the frozen
+     `mirror` / `companion` / `feedback` / `cross` partition so the overload
+     is admissibility-level rather than bookkeeping-level.
+- `[INFERRED]` Strongest claim this object is allowed to support now:
+  the repaired leakage sheet is the cleanest exact obstruction-facing object on
+  the frozen ledger, and the hostile `F_DT` comparator is already recorded as
+  an overload family in the same burden currency.
+- `[VERIFIED]` What the local record still does **not** justify:
+  a family-wide theorem for all `F_DT(delta, eta)`,
+  a claim that every repaired budget entry is hostile-sharp,
+  or an earned hostile counterexample before one explicit `F_DT` packet is
+  written on the frozen coefficient ledger.
+
+### 4. Why the two promoted objects should stay distinct at the handoff
+
+- `[INFERRED]` The repaired template object and the repaired leakage object
+  still ask different exact next questions on the same ledger:
+  the first is now a boundary-sharpness theorem test on one carried friendly
+  witness;
+  the second is an explicit hostile counterexample search in the live
+  obstruction currency.
+- `[VERIFIED]` Merging them into one Step-6 object would erase the difference
+  between
+  `G_tmpl`
+  and
+  `G_leak`,
+  and would also hide the fact that the exact missing data are different.
+
+### 5. Step-6 handoff memo
+
+- `[INFERRED]` If mission control keeps the survivor set live, the branch
+  handoff should be:
+  1. `Template-Defect Near-Closure` ->
+     first exact theorem test on the single carried witness `F_SL(1/16)`:
+     prove exact boundary saturation
+     `G_tmpl(F_SL(1/16); I) = (1/4, 49/256)`.
+  2. `Windowed Spectator-Leakage Budget` ->
+     first exact counterexample search on the single audited hostile packet
+     `F_DT(1/16, 1/256)`:
+     compute `G_leak` exactly and exhibit one repaired-budget violation on the
+     frozen ledger.
+- `[INFERRED]` Outcome status for this exploration:
+  `succeeded`.
+  Both promoted Step-6 objects received a first honest next-test assignment
+  without changing packet semantics, witnesses, hostile comparator class, or
+  repaired thresholds.
+
+## Dead Ends / Rejected Paths
+
+- `[VERIFIED]` I rejected a family-wide theorem question for
+  `Template-Defect Near-Closure`
+  on the whole `F_SL(rho)` family.
+  The current record carries one explicit worst friendly witness
+  `F_SL(1/16)`,
+  not a uniform exact family proof.
+- `[VERIFIED]` I rejected a family-wide hostile theorem question for
+  `Windowed Spectator-Leakage Budget`
+  on all of `F_DT(delta, eta)`.
+  Without one explicit hostile coefficient ledger, that would still be only a
+  dossier-level insertion line rather than an earned theorem or counterexample.
+- `[VERIFIED]` I rejected collapsing the two survivors into one combined
+  package.
+  The frozen observables, the first honest test objects, and the missing data
+  are not the same.
+
+## Provisional Handoff
+
+- Promote two distinct Step-6 objects and hand them off exactly as recorded in
+  the Step-6 handoff memo above.

